Class StandardNatsToSparkConnectorImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.spark.streaming.receiver.Receiver<String>
      • com.logimethods.connector.nats.to_spark.NatsToSparkConnector<StandardNatsToSparkConnectorImpl>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class StandardNatsToSparkConnectorImpl
extends NatsToSparkConnector<StandardNatsToSparkConnectorImpl>
    A NATS to Spark Connector.

    It will transfer messages received from NATS into Spark data.

    That class extends Receiver<String>.

    An usage of this class would look like this. 

     JavaStreamingContext ssc = new JavaStreamingContext(sc, new Duration(2000));
 final JavaReceiverInputDStream<String> messages = ssc.receiverStream(NatsToSparkConnector.receiveFromNats(StorageLevel.MEMORY_ONLY(), DEFAULT_SUBJECT));
